Oh look! The thing went offline about an hour ago, but came back online for about half a minute.
Maybe the panel charged the battery just long enough for 38 seconds of runtime. It took just a little more than two hours for that.
Guess what: It's cloudy today. I'm therefore not sure whether the (probably broken) solar panel can even generate enough power.
Let's see.
Update: I installed the new panel and it seems to be working now.
It could still go offline once the sun sets, but let's give it a chance.
Fun fact: I use the Ping integration in Home Assistant to check whether it's online or not.
The average connection time is 102 ms. Not particularly good, but also not incredibly bad.
